  "prompt": "What exactly does an Indian student need to get into any Ivy League college for post-graduate or any equivalent degree in medical sciences?",
  "response": "To get into an Ivy League college for a post-graduate medical science degree, an Indian student typically needs:\n\nAcademic Requirements:\n1. Excellent academic record\n- Minimum GPA of 3.5-4.0\n- Strong undergraduate medical/science degree\n- High grades in science subjects\n\nStandardized Test Scores:\n1. MCAT (Medical College Admission Test)\n- Competitive score (typically 510-528)\n- High percentile ranking\n\n2. GRE/GMAT (depending on specific program)\n- High percentile scores\n\nEnglish Proficiency:\n1. TOEFL/IELTS\n- Minimum TOEFL score: 100-110\n- Minimum IELTS score: 7.0-7.5\n\nAdditional Requirements:\n1. Research experience\n2. Clinical/internship exposure\n3. Strong recommendation letters\n4. Compelling personal statement\n5. Extracurricular achievements\n6. Leadership experiences\n7. Published research papers (beneficial)\n\nFinancial Considerations:\n1. Significant financial resources\n2. Scholarship applications\n3. Competitive funding opportunities\n\nApplication Process:\n1. Early application submission\n2. Comprehensive documentation\n3. Interview preparation\n\nEach Ivy League institution might have slightly different specific requirements.",
